    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>47</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>; republished by 
                    <bibl>Morelli, <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>284</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>, as unpublished;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>106200</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#masson1967"/>, p. <citedRange>225, footnote 3</citedRange></bibl> and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#marengo1985"/><citedRange/></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63779"><name nymRef="#Εὐαγόρας">Εὐαγόρας</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62829"><name nymRef="#Ἀμώμητος" type="patronymic">Ἀμωμήτω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Euagoras fils d'Amômètos</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Euagoras son of Amometos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Euagoras figlio di Amometos.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Ths stone, said to have been found «face down on Northern Acropolis» (<bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>47</citedRange></bibl>), belongs evidently to the series of funerary steles. It is thus plausible
                that it had been brought there either from the Northern or from the Western Necropolis for a re-use.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
